KAREN LECRAFT HENDERSON, Circuit Judge: In Olmstead v. L.C. ex rel. Zimring, the United States Supreme Court held that the unjustified segregation of disabled individuals in institutions is a form of disability discrimination barred by federal law. 527 U.S. 581 (1999). Consequently, the District of Columbia (“District”) violates the Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990 (ADA), Pub L No. 101-336, 104 Stat.
After a nine-day bench trial, the district court entered judgment in favor of the District. We now reverse and remand.
